# 10. 変人、本領発揮

Rui: Yes, I see where you're going with this script. Pegasus Odyssey is an orthodox heroic epic.
Rui: The protagonist, Prince Pegasus, embarks on a journey to slay the demon lord who has been causing great suffering to the people of his kingdom.
Rui: Pegasus finds new allies on his travels. His first great deed is saving a village from a terrifying dragon.
Rui: Many adventures later, the prince duels the demon lord. He prevails and returns to his town as a hero.
Rui: Tsukasa, I have some ideas for this play. Would you like to hear them?
Tsukasa: Oh, you already have something? Tell me, then, I'm curious.
Rui: I'd like to emphasize the hardships the prince must suffer on his journey to make the audience sympathize with him more.
Tsukasa: Hmm, yes.
Rui: I think some lightning strikes would be excellent for this purpose.
Tsukasa: Hmm, yes... No, hold on!
Emu: Zippy zaps! That's sooo cool!
Rui: Right? I brought along this plasma generator—
Tsukasa: Wait a minute! Why do you even have a gizmo like that?!
Rui: Oh, I thought it might come in handy.
Tsukasa: Who'd think that, ever?! Not to mention this must be incredibly dangerous!
Rui: Don't worry, the device can be securely attached to the stage in a way that will keep the audience perfectly safe. Please make sure you don't touch it or you'll die.
Tsukasa: What about keeping ME safe?!
Robo-Nene: And so it starts again...
Emu: What does?
Robo-Nene: When Rui gets excited about an idea for a show, he just has to try it out.
Robo-Nene: He tried suspending classmates from ropes in the school gym, or holding them underwater in the pool...
Robo-Nene: Everyone soon regrets signing up to do shows with him and starts to avoid him.
Emu: But why? It all sounds fun to me!
Robo-Nene: Maybe that's the problem, that there aren't more people as enthusiastic as you are, Emu...
Tsukasa: I'm not going to risk my life on-stage!
Rui: But you said you'd perform any role I gave you to, quote, “12,000%”, unquote!
Rui: I'm afraid that I have no choice but to step down as a stage director. Nene, good luck working with these people.
Emu: Whaaat? We won't be doing the zippy zaps? But lightning bolts on stage would easily be the highlight of our play!
Tsukasa: Highlight?!
Tsukasa: Hmm. I can see how they would make it an electrifying performance in more ways than one... It would be an unprecedented spectacle, sure to draw attention.
Emu: And then we'd have lots and lots of people coming to see our show!
Tsukasa: Ngh!
Tsukasa: Rui... If it's just a few little lightning bolts, maybe we could give it a try.
Rui: Hm?
Tsukasa: It's not because an electric show like that would make me famous! But I think that innovation is key to excellent theater!
Rui: I see... Well, in that case...
Rui: How about also adding some realism to the dragon fight scene by means of a modified flamethrower?
Tsukasa: A...flamethrower?!
Rui: The final battle with the demon lord could be made more epic if you were launched ten meters into the air before landing to deliver the final blow.
Rui: I've recently constructed a powerful air jet which can be installed in the stage floor.
Tsukasa: Do you have any suggestions that AREN'T extremely hazardous?
Tsukasa: B-But... They would certainly wow the audience. As a true star, I should be able to rise to the challenge!
Emu: Yaaay! All of these ideas are amazing! Do you have any more?
Rui: Well, since this is an outdoor stage, we could construct a waterfall...
Robo-Nene: Don't encourage him or he'll get out of control...
Tsukasa: Phew... We had so much to talk about, it took up the entire day...
Tsukasa: We'll meet here tomorrow at 7:00AM! Check before you leave that you haven't forgotten your staff cards!
Emu, Rui & Robo-Nene: See you tomorrow!
Nene: I haven't seen you in such a good mood in a while.
Rui: Who, me? I'm always in a good mood.
Rui: Nene, I'm heading the other way. See you tomorrow.
Nene: Oh? You're not going home yet?
Rui: No. I need to buy some more parts for modding some stage equipment. I have my work cut out for me.
Nene: ..... He really seems happy.
Tsukasa: *Huff*... *Huff*... *Huff*...
Robo-Nene: Interesting. I thought all that was remarkable about you was the size of your ego, but you're not too bad at acting and dance.
Rui: Yes, that was passable, but this style of fighting seems too bland for Prince Pegasus. You need to use your whole body to make it more expressive.
Tsukasa: I'll try it another way... How about now!
Rui: That's much better movement, but it only makes the other areas you're lacking in more apparent.
Tsukasa: *Huff*... *Huff*... I'm spent!
Rui: Oh? So soon?
Tsukasa: Uh! I've hired a tyrannical director...
Robo-Nene: What's the problem, “future super-star”? Was that the best you could do?
Tsukasa: No, of course not! But I wish you gave me some hints on how to improve...
Emu: Oh! I know where we could go for ideas!
Rui: Yes? And where would that be?
Emu: Miku's SEKAI! I have this song on my phone, “Untitled,” that I can play to take us there instantly!
Robo-Nene: What?
Tsukasa: You have “Untitled” on your phone too?! You're seriously suggesting we go to that crazy place again?!
Emu: It just appeared on my phone before I knew it! Tsukasa, let's introduce Rui and Robo-Nene to Miku and KAITO!
Tsukasa: No! Stop! I don't wanna go!
